lefield, Berkshire, England":"Englefield, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom","France":"France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Englefield","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from either of two places called Englefield (in Berks and Surrey).  Compare  Inglefield  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ingarfield","meanings":["English: locative name,  see  Englefield  ."]},{"name":"Inglefield","meanings":["English: locative name from Englefield (Surrey), recorded as  <i>Ingelfeld</i> in 1282, or Englefield (Berks)."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Englefield was born in 1270, in Englefield, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir John de Englefield, was 51 and his mother, Burgia De Englefield, was 46. He had at least 3 sons with Margery de Englefield. He died in 1306, in France, at the age of 36."},"et":{"1270–1306":"1270–1306","–Female":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1279–Female":"1279–Surnud","1292–1362":"1292–1362","1294–Male":"1294–Surnud","1296–Male":"1296–Surnud","1220–1276":"1220–1276","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1220":"1220","1296":"1296","1362":"1362","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","1292":"1292","ABT 1294":"umbes 1294","ABT 1296":"umbes 1296","1225":"1225","1279":"1279","1276":"1276","Abt 1292":"umbes 1292","1306":"1306","Englefield, Berkshire, England":"Englefield, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of,Englefield,Berkshire,England":"Englefield, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of, Englefield, Berkshire, England":"Englefield, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1270–1306":"1270–1306","–Female":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1279–Female":"1279–Kuollut","1292–1362":"1292–1362","1294–Male":"1294–Kuollut","1296–Male":"1296–Kuollut","1220–1276":"1220–1276","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1220":"1220","1296":"1296","1362":"1362","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","1292":"1292","ABT 1294":"noin 1294","ABT 1296":"noin 1296","1225":"1225","1279":"1279","1276":"1276","Abt 1292":"noin 1292","1306":"1306","Englefield, Berkshire, England":"Englefield, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of,Englefield,Berkshire,England":"Englefield, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of, Englefield, Berkshire, England":"Englefield, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"1270–1306":"1270–1306","–Female":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1279–Female":"1279–Décédée","1292–1362":"1292–1362","1294–Male":"1294–Décédé","1296–Mal